{"title":"LRU semantics: summary vs detail","gitnotes":1,"type":"html","body":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<style>\n  :root { --bg:#0f1419; --fg:#e7ecf3; --muted:#8899a6; --accent:#1d9bf0; --panel:#192734; --border:#38444d; }\n  body { font:15px/1.5 system-ui,sans-serif; background:var(--bg); color:var(--fg); margin:0; padding:1.5rem 2rem; max-width:48rem; }\n  h1 { font-size:1.3rem; margin:0 0 1rem; }\n  .tabs { display:flex; gap:.5rem; margin-bottom:1rem; }\n  .tabs button { background:var(--panel); border:1px solid var(--border); color:var(--fg); padding:.45rem .9rem; border-radius:6px; cursor:pointer; font:inherit; }\n  .tabs button.active { background:var(--accent); border-color:var(--accent); color:#fff; }\n  .panel { display:none; background:var(--panel); border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:8px; padding:1rem 1.15rem; }\n  .panel.active { display:block; }\n  code { background:#0003; padding:.1rem .35rem; border-radius:4px; font-size:.9em; }\n  ul { margin:.5rem 0; padding-left:1.2rem; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>LRU get/set review</h1>\n<div class=\"tabs\">\n  <button type=\"button\" class=\"active\" data-tab=\"summary\">Summary</button>\n  <button type=\"button\" data-tab=\"detail\">Detail</button>\n</div>\n<div id=\"summary\" class=\"panel active\">\n  <p>Eviction uses native <code>Map</code> insertion order — no extra linked list. Safe for demo sizes; revisit if we benchmark huge caches.</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>get</strong> refreshes key to MRU on hit</li>\n    <li><strong>set</strong> evicts LRU when at capacity</li>\n    <li><strong>stats()</strong> exposes hit/miss counters</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"detail\" class=\"panel\">\n  <p>On <code>get</code>, a hit deletes and re-inserts the entry so it becomes the newest key. Misses increment <code>misses</code> only.</p>\n  <p>On <code>set</code> with a full cache, <code>store.keys().next()</code> yields the LRU key. The optional <code>onEvict</code> callback fires <em>before</em> the new entry is stored — useful for logging or secondary invalidation.</p>\n  <p>Updating an existing key does not count as an eviction; it simply reorders.</p>\n</div>\n<script>\ndocument.querySelectorAll('.tabs button').forEach(function(btn) {\n  btn.addEventListener('click', function() {\n    document.querySelectorAll('.tabs button').forEach(function(b) { b.classList.remove('active'); });\n    document.querySelectorAll('.panel').forEach(function(p) { p.classList.remove('active'); });\n    btn.classList.add('active');\n    document.getElementById(btn.dataset.tab).classList.add('active');\n  });\n});\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"}
